The paper deals with a multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) multiple access channel (MAC) and derives deterministic approximations of various performance metrics. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of random matrices and large random matrix theory, which are topics commonly studied in the Mathematics of Computing (cs.MM) sub-category. The paper also discusses power allocation and interference control, which are relevant to the Signal Processing (cs.SI) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on channel models and performance analysis could also place it in the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category.
